{"lemma": "أَحَدّ", "slug": "أَحَدّ", "root": "#.ح.د", "root_slug": "_-ح-د", "root_link": "/words/roots/_-ح-د", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "أَحَدّ", "root": "أحد", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 74}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 9, "pos_tags": ["adj", "name", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 13}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n333", "", "", "n7288"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "one", "fa": "یک", "ur": "ایک", "tr": "bir", "id": "satu", "bn": "এক", "es": "uno", "fr": "un", "de": "eins", "ru": "один", "zh": "一"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "one", "examples": [{"text": "أَحَدٌ وَعِشْرُونَ", "english": "twenty-one"}, {"text": "إِحْدَى وَعِشْرُونَ", "english": "twenty-one"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "one of"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "اَلْأَحَد (al-ʔaḥad): ellipsis of يَوْم الْأَحَد (yawm al-ʔaḥad, “Sunday”, literally “day one”)", "tags": ["definite"], "examples": [{"text": "لكنه عاد للعمل في صباح الأحد", "english": "but he was back to work on Sunday morning"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a person; somebody, someone; anybody, anyone", "examples": [{"text": "هَلْ مِنْ أَحَدٍ هُنَا؟", "english": "Is there anyone here?"}, {"text": "قُلْ هُوَ ٱللَّهُ أَحَدٌ ٱللَّهُ ٱلصَّمَدُ لَمْ يَلِدْ وَلَمْ يُولَدْ وَلَمْ يَكُن لَهُۥ كُفُوًا أَحَدٌ", "english": "Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “He is Allah—One ˹and Indivisible˺; Allah—the Sustainer ˹needed by all˺. He has never had offspring, nor was He born. And there is none comparable to Him."}]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "one", "examples": [{"text": "قُلْ هُوَ ٱللَّهُ أَحَدٌ ٱللَّهُ ٱلصَّمَدُ لَمْ يَلِدْ وَلَمْ يُولَدْ وَلَمْ يَكُن لَهُۥ كُفُوًا أَحَدٌ", "english": "Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “He is Allah—One ˹and Indivisible˺; Allah—the Sustainer ˹needed by all˺. He has never had offspring, nor was He born. And there is none comparable to Him."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to sharpen"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "elative degree of حَادّ (ḥādd):; more acute, sharper, more cutting; most acute, sharpest, most cutting; very acute, sharp or cutting"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "elative degree of حَادّ (ḥādd):; more vehement; most vehement; very vehement"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "elative degree of حَدّ (ḥadd)"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "elative degree of حَدّ (ḥadd):; more violent, more passionate; most violent, most passionate; very violent, very passionate"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "fierce"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "with sharp teeth"}, {"pos": "name", "gloss": "a mountain north of Medina, Saudi Arabia"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Related to the root و ح د (w ḥ d) of وَاحِد (wāḥid, “one”), from Proto-Semitic *ʾaḥad-. Cognate with Hebrew אֶחָד (ekhád, “one”).\n\nElative of حَادّ (ḥādd, “sharp, vehement”) and حَدّ (ḥadd, “violent, passionate”)."}, "ipa": ["/ʔa.ħad/", "/ʔa.ħadd/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n333", "headword_ar": "اَحَدٌ", "root": "AHd", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waHadN", "text_ar": "وَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "first of the numbers;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;) syn. [in many cases] with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Msb, K;) with which it is interchangeable in two cases, to be explained below: (Msb:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=HaAdN", "text_ar": "ا=حَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^NHodaAnN", "text_ar": "اٌحْدَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHaduwna", "text_ar": "اَحَدُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which last occurs in a phrase hereafter to be mentioned; (TA;) or it has no pl. in this sense; (Msb, K, * TA;) and as to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=HaAdN", "text_ar": "ا=حَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", it may be pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [and originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^awoHaAdN", "text_ar": "اَوْحَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$ohaAdN", "text_ar": "اَشْهَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aAhidN", "text_ar": "شَاهِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Th, Msb,) a pl. of pauc. (Msb.) The fem. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "only; and this is only used in particular cases, to be shown below: (Msb:) most agree that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this word is the characteristic of the fem. gender: but some say that it is to render it quasi-coordinate to the quadriliteral-radical class: [this, however, is inconsistent with its pronunciation, which is invariably"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHod~aY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] (TA:) its pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHadN", "text_ar": "اـِحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as though the sing. were"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodapN", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as is said of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*ikarN", "text_ar": "ذِكَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*ikoraY", "text_ar": "ذِكْرَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": one of the expositors of the Tes-heel writes it"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uHadN", "text_ar": "اُحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with damm and then fet-h; but a pl. of this measure is not applicable to a sing. of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiEolaY", "text_ar": "فِعْلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with kesr. (MF.) The dim. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uHayodN", "text_ar": "اُحَيْدٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and that of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uHayodaY", "text_ar": "اُحَيْدَى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (L in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wHd", "text_ar": "وحد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b2-  It is interchangeable with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in two cases: first, when it is used as an epithet applied to God: (Msb:) for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHadu", "text_ar": "الاَحَدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as an epithet, is applied to God alone, (Msb, K,) and signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The One; the Sole; He who has ever been one and alone:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the Indivisible:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He who has no second"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to share"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in his lordship, nor in his essence, nor in his attributes:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa AlwaAHidu", "text_ar": "هُوَ الوَاحِدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa AlA^aHadu", "text_ar": "هُوَ الاَحَدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", without the article, is used as an epithet specially in relation to God, and is interchangeable in this case [but not in other cases] with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": therefore you do not say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajulN A^aHadN", "text_ar": "رَجُلٌ اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "nor"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dirohamN A^aHadN", "text_ar": "دِرْهَمٌ اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the like [but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajulN", "text_ar": "رَجُلٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHdN", "text_ar": "وَاحدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dirhamN waAHidN", "text_ar": "دِرهَمٌ وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.] (Msb.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wHd", "text_ar": "وحد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] In the phrase in the Kur [cxii. 1],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qulo huwa All~`hu A^aHadN", "text_ar": "قُلْ هُوَ اللّٰهُ اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Say, He is God, One"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "God],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a substitute for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "All~`hu", "text_ar": "اللّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for an indeterminate noun is sometimes a substitute for a determinate noun, as in another passage in the Kur, xcvi. 15 and 16. (S.) Secondly, it is interchangeable with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in certain nouns of number: (Msb:) you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHada Ea$ara", "text_ar": "اَحَدَ عَشَرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[masc.] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY Ea$orapa", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى عَشْرَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[fem.] (S) [meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Eleven:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and in these two cases you may not substitute"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidapN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but] in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadNwEa$oruwna", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌوعَشْرُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One and twenty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the like,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is interchangeable with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) Ks says, When you prefix the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to a number, prefix it to every number; therefore you should say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA faEalati AlA^aHada AlEa$ara", "text_ar": "مَا فَعَلَتِ الاَحَدَ العَشَرَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^alofa Ald~irohama", "text_ar": "الاَلْفَ الدِّرْهَمَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What did the eleven thousand dirhems?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: but the Basrees prefix it to the first only, and say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA fElt AlA^aHada Ea$ara A^alofa dirohamK", "text_ar": "ما فعلت الاَحَدَ عَشَرَ اَلْفَ دِرْهَمٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) ―         -b3-  In [most] cases differing from these two, there is a difference in usage between"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the former is used in affirmative phrases as a prefixed noun only, governing the noun which follows it in the gen. case; [as in exs. which will be found below;] and is used absolutely in negative phrases; [as will also be seen in exs. below;] whereas"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used in affirmative phrases as a prefixed noun and otherwise: the fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also, is only used as a prefixed noun, except in numbers (Msb) [and in one other instance, which see below]. Using"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and its fem. in affirmative phrases as prefixed nouns, you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAma A^aHadu Alv~alaAvapi", "text_ar": "قَامَ اَحَدُ الثَّلَاثَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One of the three stood"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAlato A_iHodaA humaA", "text_ar": "قَالَتْ اـِحْدَا هُمَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One of them two"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(females)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "said"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xu*o A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "خُذْ اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alv~alaAvapi", "text_ar": "الثَّلَاثَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Take thou one of the three"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) The phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY banaAti TabaqK", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى بَنَاتِ طَبَقٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A calamity:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or, as some say, (TA, but in the K “ and, ”)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a serpent;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA;) so called because it twists itself round so as to become like a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tabaq", "text_ar": "طَبَق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) And the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY AlA_iHadi", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى الاـِحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (L, K, TA,) in which the latter word has kesr to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_", "text_ar": "اـ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and fet-h to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "H", "text_ar": "ح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and is pl. of the former, also written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^uHadi", "text_ar": "الاُحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but this form is disapproved by MF, as has been shown above, (TA, [in several copies of the K incorrectly written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHadi", "text_ar": "الاَحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]) [lit. means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One of the ones;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and] is applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a great,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mighty, event;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one that is difficult, distressing, grievous,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "terrible."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ataY biA_iHodaY AlA_iHadi", "text_ar": "اَتَى بِاـِحْدَى الاـِحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[the last of which words is here again written in several copies of the K"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHadi", "text_ar": "الاَحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He brought to pass a grievous, and great,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mighty, event,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,) when you desire to express the greatness and terribleness of an event. (TA.) You also say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnu A^aHadu AlA^aHadiyna", "text_ar": "فُلَانُ اَحَدُ الاَحَدِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidu AlA^aHadiyna", "text_ar": "وَاحِدُ الاَحَدِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) the latter in one copy of the K written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidu AlwaAHidiyna", "text_ar": "وَاحِدُ الوَاحِدِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in which the latter word is pl. of the former, (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidu", "text_ar": "وَاحِدُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA=HaAdi", "text_ar": "الا=حَادِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY AlA_iHadi", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى الاـِحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,) like a phrase before mentioned, only the former is applied to a calamity, and this to an intelligent being, and written in the two manners before mentioned, the difference being only in application, (TA, [in several copies of the K here again written"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHadi", "text_ar": "الاَحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AaHadiY~u AlAaHadi", "text_ar": "اَحَدِىُّ الاَحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHadiyna", "text_ar": "الاَحَدِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Et-Tes-heel,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY AlA=HaAdi", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى الا=حَادِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) which are expressions of the utmost praise, (IAar, A Heyth, K,) [lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a man is one of the ones;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such a one is unique among the uniques;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one who has no equal; unequalled; incomparable."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, Tes-heel.) It seems that the form of pl. used in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadu AlA^aHadiyna", "text_ar": "اَحَدُ الاَحَدِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used only as applied to rational beings; but it is said in the Expositions of the Tes-heel that this phrase signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One of the calamities;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the form of the rational pl. being given to nouns significant of things deemed great, mighty, or grievous. (AHeyth.) In the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY AlA_iHadi", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى الاـِحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the fem. forms are said to be used for the purpose of giving intensiveness to the signification, as though the meaning were"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAhiyapu Ald~awaAhiY", "text_ar": "دَاهِيَةُ الدَّوَاهِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the word"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAhyp", "text_ar": "داهية"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being [an intensive epithet] from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dahaA='N", "text_ar": "دَهَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as signifying intelligence, or intelligence mixed with craft or cunning and forecast; or by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAhyp", "text_ar": "داهية"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being meant a calamity. (Expositions of the Fs, TA.) AHei thought"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadu AlA^aHadiyna", "text_ar": "اَحَدُ الاَحَدِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to be an epithet applied to a male, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY AlA_iHadi", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى الاـِحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to be applied to a female: but his opinion has been refuted by EdDemámeenee in the Expos. of the Tes-heel: and this latter author there remarks, that in expressions meant to denote praise [of a man],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are prefixed to their own proper pls., as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHaduwna", "text_ar": "اَحَدُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHadN", "text_ar": "اـِحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; or to an epithet, as in the case of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadu AlEulamaA='i", "text_ar": "اَحَدُ العُلَمَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One of the learned"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; but that they have not been heard prefixed to generic nouns. (TA.) You say likewise,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa A@bonu A_iHodaAhaA", "text_ar": "هُوَ ا@بْنُ اـِحْدَاهَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He is born of noble,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "generous, ancestors, both on the father's and the mother's side;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "speaking of a man and of a camel. (L and K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wHd", "text_ar": "وحد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA yaquwmu bih`*aA AlA^amori A_il~aA A@bonu A_iHodaAhaA", "text_ar": "لَا يَقُومُ بِهٰذَا الاَمْرِ اـِلَّا ا@بْنُ اـِحْدَاهَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "None will manage this thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affair, but a noble,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "generous, man."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ, L in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wHd", "text_ar": "وحد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA yasotaTiyEuhaA", "text_ar": "لَا يَسْتَطِيعُهَا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@bonu A_iHodAtihaA", "text_ar": "ا@بْنُ اـِحْداتِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "None will be able to perform it but a noble,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "generous, man"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (L in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wHd", "text_ar": "وحد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b4-  One instance is mentioned, of the occurrence, in a trad., of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "not used as a part of a number [i. e. not as a part of the compound"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY Ea$orapa", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى عَشْرَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] nor as a prefixed noun; viz.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHodaY mino saboEK", "text_ar": "اـِحْدَى مِنْ سَبْعٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "One of seven"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; in which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sbE", "text_ar": "سبع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said to mean the nights of 'Ád [during which that tribe was destroyed], or the years of Joseph [during which Egypt was afflicted with dearth]. (MF, from the Fáïk &c.) ―         -b5-  Used in a negative phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Any one with whom one may talk or speak:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and in this manner it is used without variation as sing. and pl. and fem. (S) as well as masc. (Msb.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A^aHada fiy Ald~aAri", "text_ar": "لَا اَحَدَ فِي الدَّارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There is not any one in the house"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: but you do not say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhaA A^aHadN", "text_ar": "فِيهَا اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as meaning the contrary]. (S.) We read in the Kur [lxix. 47, this ex. of its use as a masc. pl.],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famaA minokumo mino A^aHadK Eanohu HaAjiziyna", "text_ar": "فَمَا مِنْكُمْ مِنْ اَحَدٍ عَنْهُ حَاجِزِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And not any persons of you should have withheld me from"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "punishing"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "him"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.) And in the same [xxxiii. 32, we find this ex. of its use as a fem. pl.],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lasotun~a kaA^aHadK mina Aln~isaA='i", "text_ar": "لَسْتُنَّ كَاَحَدٍ مِنَ النِّسَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Ye are not like any"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "others"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of women"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.) ―         -b6-  It is also used in interrogative phrases; as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "halo A^aHadN", "text_ar": "هَلْ اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ay mivola h`*aA", "text_ar": "رَاَي مِثْلَ هٰذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Has any one seen the like of this?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (A'Obeyd, L;) and in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA Hado raA=haA", "text_ar": "يَا حَدْ رَا=هَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA A^aHadN", "text_ar": "يَا اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O, has any one seen her,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (L, from a trad.) ―         -b7-  It is [said to be] also used in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aY'N", "text_ar": "شَىءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anything"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], applied to an irrational being; as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA biA ld~aAri mino A^aHadK", "text_ar": "مَا بِا لدَّارِ مِنْ اَحَدٍ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_il~aA HimaArFA", "text_ar": "اـِلَّا حِمَارًا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There is not in the house anything,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "rational or irrational,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "except an ass:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so that the thing excepted is united in kind to that from which the exception is made [accord. to this rendering; but this instance is generally regarded as one in which the thing excepted is disunited in kind from that from which the exception is made]."}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 28}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) So too in the Kur lx. 11, accord. to the reading of Ibn-Mes'ood: (Msb:) but others there read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aYo'N", "text_ar": "شَىْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which may mean any one or any thing. (Bd, Jel.) ―         -b8-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aHadN", "text_ar": "الاَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawoma AlA^aHadi", "text_ar": "يَوْمَ الاَحَدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb,) as a proper name, (Msb,) is applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain day;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Sunday;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the first day of the week;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or, as some say, [i. e. as some term it,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the second of the week;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) for the Arabs are said, by IAar, to have reckoned the Sabbath, or Saturday, as the first, though they called Sunday the first of the days: (Msb in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jmE", "text_ar": "جمع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) it is sing., and masc.: (Lh:) pl. [as above, i. e.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=HaAdN", "text_ar": "ا=حَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uHodaAnN", "text_ar": "اُحْدَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) or it has no pl. (K: [but in the TA this last observation is very properly restricted, as relating only to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadN", "text_ar": "اَحَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and as applied to any unknown person.]) In this sense, it has no dim. (Sb, in S, art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ams", "text_ar": "امس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA=HaAdu", "text_ar": "الا=حَادُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in lexicology signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What have been transmitted by some of the lexicologists, but not by such a number of them as cannot be supposed to have agreed to a falsehood:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "what has been transmitted by this larger number is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mutawaAtiru", "text_ar": "مُتَوَاتِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Mz 3rd"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nwE", "text_ar": "نوع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "K", "Th", "TA", "S", "L", "Lh"]}, {"entry_id": "n7288", "headword_ar": "اَحَدُّ", "root": "Hd", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "More,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "most, sharp:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.] ―         -b2-  You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa mino A^aHad~i Alr~ijaAli", "text_ar": "هُوَ مِنْ اَحَدِّ الرِّجَالِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He is of the most sharp,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hasty, in temper,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the most irascible, passionate,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "angry, of men."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.)"}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}